data.content:
## What breaks in .NET 11

In .NET 10, the Cosmos DB provider deprecated synchronous query execution behind an opt-in flag (`EnableSyncOverAsync` or similar). **In .NET 11 (EF Core 11), that opt-in is removed entirely.** All synchronous LINQ operators on the Cosmos provider now throw `InvalidOperationException` unconditionally.

**Affected calls in your code:**
- `ToList()` → use `ToListAsync()`
- `First()` → use `FirstAsync()`
- `Count()` → use `CountAsync()`
- `SaveChanges()` → use `SaveChangesAsync()`

## Migrated code

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

**Key points:**
- `async Task<T>` return types replace synchronous returns
- All callers up the chain must also become `async`/`await`
- Remove the old `EnableSyncOverAsync` configuration — it's no longer recognized
- The relational providers (SQL Server, PostgreSQL, etc.) still support sync APIs; this is Cosmos-specific
